race.comment: SHINOHARA (10) was a sharp improver here third-up last time when battling on gamely into a close fifth. Gets in light again and looks ready to land her second win. NORMIE NO SHOW (4) stuck on bravely over 2000m at Murray Bridge. Easier company this time and he can get the job done. RAZELLA (9) was good when resuming at Clare but hasn't really gone on with it. Gets weight relief with the 3kg claimer and the rise in trip should suit. DANORO PRINCE (1) only warmed to his task late here second-up. This trip suits third-up and if he can settle closer he'll be hard to hold out. AGREEANCE (6) will find this easier but will likely be forced back from the wide draw. Expect her to be charging late. NOYERS (5) disappointed last time but was solid fresh. Worth another chance third-up over a more suitable journey.
